info.description: Auction off bingo sheets and scramble to fill them out before the game comes to a close.
info.helpText:
When all players have taken a seat, press the Setup button. Each player starts with 22 coins in a hidden personal supply (beneath the ? symbols), and one card in their hand. Players also start with one basic, uncomplete card already in their personal play area. If you mistakenly press the Setup without all players seated, you will need to reload the game.

To begin your turn, draw one card from the deck into your hand, and choose one of your two cards to place in the holder labelled Auction. If you bid a value listed on a card in your personal area, drag a coin from your supply onto that slot. If any player bids a value listed on the card in the middle, drag a coin from the bank onto that slot.

When a player wins an auction, drag the card in the center onto any available space in your play area. You can click on the number attached to your coin pile to precisely split off your bid value, then drag that new stack into the yellow payment box for the auctioneer to collect, or directly into the bank if you were the auctioneer. When your turn is over, press the End Turn button to cycle turn order. This will help keep track of who is up next as auctioneer.

When all bid slots on a card in your play area have been filled, press the Complete button associated with that holder. This will move the card into your score pile, and the coins into your supply.

As soon as the 'Fin' card has been drawn from the deck, the player that did so immediately reveals that card and announces that the game is over. Use the score trackers to add up the values of your completed cards, leftover coins, and any star bonus. Remember that each player must complete at least one card with a star value to be eligible to win.
